H iS THREATENED\nRussia and England Have Warned the\nPersian Ruler That Unless Or\nder Is Restored the Powers\nWill Have Him De\nthroned\nSpecial to the Herald\nTeheran Persia June 25 The\nshahs troops an holding the town\nand are preventing a revolt for the\ntime being The shah is acting arbi\ntrarily and has ordered the execution\nof all those participating in the upris\ning Hundreds have been jailed\nthroughout the country Reformers\nare aiousing the people and the reb\nels are reported marching on the city\nfrom the north Troops have been\nsent to meet them\nOrder Must Be Restored\nSpecial to the Herald\nSt Petersburg June 25 Russia\nand England have warned the shah\nthat unless order is restored and out\nrages cease he will he dethroned by\nthe powers and his uncle Prince Zill\nexsultan will be made ruler\niNS\nImproved It Is Expected the Patient\nWill Be Able to Leave the Hos\npital Within a Week\nv as\nSpecial to the Herald\nCleveland Ohio June 25 Con\ngressman Shermans condition is im\nproved His temperature respiration\nand pulse are better and he passed a\ncomfortable night It is expected he\nwill be able to leave the hospital in\na week and the physicians have de\ncided no operation will be necessary\nnow The specialists who were sum\nmoned have been directed to not\ncome\niy\nPALESTINE TEXAS THURSDAY AFTERNOON JUNE 25 1908\nMEYER MAY GET JOB\nEspecial to the Herald\nI Oyster Bay N Y June 25\nIt is reported that Postmast\njer General Meyer may be se\nlected as chairman of the re\npublican national committee\nfit is said that Taft and Rooso\nvelt both favor his appoint\ni ment which may be an\nnounced Saturday\nA A A A A A A A\nCLEVELANDS FUNERAL\nServices Will Be Extremely Simple\nOnly Invited Persons Being\nAllowed to Attend\nr t\nz\nxxJLjJlJ\n15 CTS A WEEK\nThe beckoning smile of opportunity is found in Herald ads Read them Profit by them\nThe Coldest the Purest and the Greatest\nVariety in Cold Drinks Ices and Creams at\nBOOT\nOf course Everything in Candies\nUnion Made\nTHE PALESTINE OUEE\n5c\nexas Grown Tobacco\nh Mmm\n5c\nYour Dealer Has It\nGibson to Hang Saturday\nCuero Texas June 21 The execu\ntion of Monk Gibson will take place\nhere Saturday probably between the\nhours of 230 and 3 oclock and it is\nexpected that a special train will\nbring up people from Wharton and in\nteimediate points who wish to wit\nness it and return home the same\nday\nMinnesota Governor and Judge Gray\nWill Not Give Up the Fight\nCandidates For Vice Presi\ndent Are Becoming\nNumerous\nSpecial to the Herald\nDenver Colo June 25 Jacob Wal\ndeck concspondent of the United\nPi ess in re iewing the democratic\noutlook says Bijans nomination for\nthe presidency is as good as made\nHo says there was never anything\nsurer in politics\nRiyans friends count on at least\n750 of the lOOS delegates with G72\nnecessary to nominate The ft lends\nof Governor Johnson and Indue Gray\naio still fighting Johnson headquar\nters have been opened He may be\nlooking lo the 1012 nomination\nFoimer Governor Douglass of Mas\nsachusetts C A Tow ne Cornelius\nIugsley of Now York Frank Kalzrn\nback of Now Joisey John W Kein of\nIndiana Congressman James of Ken\ntucky Judson Haimon of Ohio jnd\nGovernor Folk or Missouri aie all\nvice piesldential possibilities\nSpecial to the Herald\nPrinceton N J June 25 Presi\ndent Roosevelt is expected to arrive\nat noon tomorrow for the funeral ser\nvices over the remains of exPresi\ndent Cleveland The funeral is to be\nextremely simple only invited guests\nbeing allowed on the grounds The\ntown is filled with visitors to pay a\nlast tribute to the illustrious dead\nThS body will noalie in state\nMrs Clevelands bearing up well\nEsther and Marion the two oldest\nchildren will arrive tonight\nThe following pallbearers have\nbeen announced Paul Morton E C\nBenedict Dr Henry Vandyke John\nHibben Prof Andrew West Presi\nTl ylt Finley of New York College\nTile route of the funeral will be\nroped off and guarded bypolice and\nmi 